📊 Task 01 - Bar Chart & Histogram Visualization
This project is a simple data visualization task aimed at creating bar charts to represent the distribution of categorical and continuous variables using Python.

📝 Task Description
Objective:
Create a bar chart or histogram to visualize the distribution of a categorical or continuous variable, such as the distribution of ages or genders in a population.

Based on the Task Image:

Distribution by gender

Distribution by age groups

🧪 Requirements
Install the required libraries using:

bash

pip install pandas matplotlib
🚀 How to Run

python task_1.py
You will see:

A bar chart showing gender distribution.

A bar chart showing age group distribution.

📷 Output Example
The code will generate two charts:

Gender Distribution (skyblue for Male, pink for Female)

Age Group Distribution (light green for different age ranges: 21–30, 31–40, etc.)

